 farmers, and sustainable economic opportunities for the rural poor that in turn generate further investment. It describes the benefits of digital technologies for farmers and the challenges of transforming African agricultural policies and creating effective and inspiring leadership.Food for All in Africa demonstrates why we should take on the challenge and provides ideas and methods through which it can be met.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAgricultural intensificationzAfrica, Sub-Saharan. 0aAgricultural intensificationzAfrica. 0aFarms, SmallzAfrica, Sub-Saharan. 0aFarms, SmallzAfrica. 0aFood securityzAfrica, Sub-Saharan. 0aFood securityzAfrica. 0aProduce tradezAfrica, Sub-Saharan. 0aProduce tradezAfrica. 0aSustainable agriculturezAfrica, Sub-Saharan. 0aSustainable agriculturezAfrica. 4aAfrican Hist & Diaspora. 4aAgriculture. 4aGeneral Science.  aSustainable intensification, sustainable agriculture, Africa, Resilience, Value chains, Hybrids, Agricultural Transformation, Hunger, Malnutrition.1 aBadiane, Ousmane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGlatzel, Katrin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501744419?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/is